    "intro": "Interpretation asks what the text means — moving from observation of what it says to discernment of the author's intent in its canonical and historical context. The movements below trace Job 28's argument through its three strophes, attending to the poem's rhetorical design, its place in ancient wisdom literature, and its function within the book of Job as a whole. Where Hebrew vocabulary sharpens the meaning, a brief note follows as supplement to the exposition.",
